                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18410823-2281-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18410823-2281-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18410823-2281-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18410823-cd-282" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410823-2281-offence-1 t18410823-cd-282"></join>12th of July</rs>, 1 washing-board, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18410823-name-1559" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1559" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1559" type="surname" value="COUSINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1559" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410823-2281-offence-1 t18410823-name-1559"></join>George Cousins</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1560" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1560" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1560" type="surname" value="COUSINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1560" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE COUSINS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a gunner in the Royal Artillery. Some few weeks ago I lost a washing-board and tea-kettle from a washhouse at the back of Artillery-place—I afterwards saw the washing-board at Saville's shop, on the 2nd of July—I hat now produced is it—I his case was not taken up by the regiment, on account of the prisoner's character.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1561" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1561" type="surname" value="SAVILLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1561" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SAVILLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a broker, in Wellington-street, Woolwich, bought this washing-board of the prisoner for 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1562" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1562" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1562" type="surname" value="THOROGOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1562" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN THOROGOOD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 189.) I took the prisoner into custody—I asked him whether he knew any thing of the property I pro<lb></lb>duced—he said he knew nothing of it—I asked if he would deny it if I brought a witness who bought the property of him—he said, if that was the case, it was all well and good.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. The prosecutor and the witness are related toge<lb></lb>ther, and it is a combined thing between them against me; he does not live six doors from me; it is not likely I should steal it, and sell it to a man that knew me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1563" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1563" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1563" type="surname" value="SAVILLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1563" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SAVILLE</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. I never knew the prisoner before—I am no acquaintance of Cousins.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1564" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1564" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1564" type="surname" value="COUSINS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1564" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE COUSINS</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. He is a gunner in the regiment, the same as myself—he has a good-conduct stripe on his arm—I here has been no quarrel between us—he has been convicted twice in the regiment for theft—a man is entitled to a stripe if he is two years out of trouble—it is a long time since he was in trouble—I never knew him before this occur<lb></lb>rence—he belongs to the 9th battalion, and I to the first—the property was locked up in the washhouse—I he prisoner rented a room in the same house for a very short time—there is no one here from the regiment to give him a character—the officers are aware he is on trial—I had used this washing-board a week before—it was not thrown aside as if it was lumber—the prisoner's wife asked if we had got such a thing to lend her, and when we came to look for it it was gone—I here has been no quarrel be<lb></lb>tween his wife and mine—I he board was exposed for sale at Saville's which is not far from where I live—I know it by marks where I pulled the head off, and nailed it on again myself—I bought it in Woolwich.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18410823-2281-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
